-# Locals: organization, teammate, employee_name, manager_name
- organization = local_assigns.fetch(:organization)
- teammate = local_assigns.fetch(:teammate)
- employee_name = local_assigns.fetch(:employee_name)
- manager_name = local_assigns.fetch(:manager_name)

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    See why each 1-by-1 clarity check-in (aspiration, assignment, position) appears where it does in the queue—for
    = employee_name
    and for
    = manager_name
    —so you know what needs attention now versus what can wait.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  = render 'shared/maap/definition'
  = render 'shared/check_ins/three_step_clarity_flow', organization: organization, teammate: teammate, employee_name: employee_name

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Two perspectives
  %p.mb-2
    Each column is the same teammate’s queue computed from that person’s view (employee vs manager completion on the
    %strong open
    check-in). By default, only items that still need an action from that person are shown; use
    %strong Show the other
    at the bottom of a column to expand completed and healthy items.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Gruuv Health pill on each item
  %p.mb-2
    Next to each item name is an outline pill for that column’s person. It reflects Gruuv Health for Required Clarity on
    that item (how recently it was finalized, plus open check-in workflow when relevant). Hover the pill for the full
    explanation.
  %p.mb-2
    Pills mean:
  %ul.mb-3
    %li.d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.border.border-success.text-success.bg-transparent.flex-shrink-0 Healthy
      %span
        %em no action needed
        — finalized recently; clarity is in good shape.
    %li.d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.border.border-warning.text-warning.bg-transparent.flex-shrink-0 Warning
      %span
        %em action desired
        — finalized a while ago; an early check-in is encouraged.
    %li.d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.border.border-danger.text-danger.bg-transparent.flex-shrink-0 Needs Attention
      %span
        %em action required
        — never finalized or stale; check in now.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 How items are ordered
  %ul.mb-3
    %li Items that still need your action come first (more actions before fewer).
    %li Then by Gruuv Health urgency (Needs Attention, then Warning, then Healthy).
    %li Then by type (aspiration, assignment, position) and name.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Workflow on each item
  %p.mb-2
    Each item lists who still needs to act on the open check-in: employee and manager with a check or open circle,
    then joint review (button when both sides are done, otherwise a pending step).
  %p.mb-2
    Hover the
    %i.bi.bi-info-circle
    icon beside the name for why that item is on the list.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Clarity actions
  %p.mb-2
    Each list item ends with how many Gruuv Health actions that person still needs on that item.
  %ul.mb-3
    %li
      %strong Healthy:
      actions are counted in the spotlight total and show as completed (0 still needed).
    %li
      %strong Warning / Needs Attention:
      1 action when there is no open check-in yet (start one).
    %li
      %strong With an open check-in:
      count incomplete sides for that person; managers also count finalize when both sides are done.
    %li
      Joint review (ready to finalize together) is shown separately and is not counted here.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Example list item
  %p.mb-2.text-muted.small
    The name is a link with the Gruuv Health pill beside it; bullets below explain state.
  .border.rounded.p-3.bg-white.mb-0
    .d-flex.align-items-center.gap-2.flex-wrap.mb-2
      %span.fw-semibold Keep Growing
      %i.bi.bi-info-circle.text-muted
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.border.border-danger.text-danger.bg-transparent Needs Attention
    %ul.small.mb-0
      %li.mb-1.text-muted
        Hover the pill on the live page for the full Gruuv Health explanation.
      %li Last finalized 2 months ago.
      %li (1) #{employee_name} ○
      %li (2) #{manager_name} ○
      %li (3) Both complete? Review together ○
      %li= "1 action required from #{employee_name}"
